If you define a class method as an lambda function instead of the normal syntax the syntax highlight can get confused if you use Allman style braces instead of K&R bracing.

Steps to Reproduce:
1.  Create a type script file and add a class.
2. Define a method in this class using the lambda syntax with Allman indenting:

``` typescript
class MyType
{
    public myFunction = (): void =>
    {
        // From this point on the syntax highlighting will be confused as to where it is.
        var myVar = 5;
        console.log("Hello there!");
    }
}
```

If you define a function with K&R style braces it works okay:

``` typescript
class MyType
{
    public myFunction = (): void => {
        // Syntax highlighting is OK now? :/
        var myVar = 5;
        console.log("Hello there!");
    }
}
```
